"{\"uid\": \"citizen.co.za-sport-medal-hopes-team-sa-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Home\\u00bbSport  ByWesley Botton  Chief sports journalist  5 minute read  22 July 2024  12:35 pm  Tatjana Smith will lead South Africa's medal charge at the Olympic Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\", \"score\": 0.901131173431149, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Botton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\"}, {\"begin\": 117, \"end\": 129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999992311698633, \"rank\": 7.669689042395136e-07, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 169, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.1285026751789862e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Picture: Anton Geyser/Gallo Images  Team South Africa will not be targeting a record medal haul at the Olympic Games in Paris, but they will be confident of securing at least a few podium places at the quadrennial Games which officially opens on Friday.\", \"from\": 176, \"to\": 429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 191, \"end\": 197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geyser\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.263721540895044e-19, \"text\": \"Geyser\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geyser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geyser\"}, {\"begin\": 198, \"end\": 203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gallo_Record_Company\", \"score\": 0.9709826687687942, \"rank\": 0.027973977835379943, \"text\": \"Gallo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gallo_Record_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gallo_Record_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 212, \"end\": 229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Team South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 296, \"end\": 301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.1285026751789862e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We take a look at five of the nation's top medal hopes in the French capital over the next few weeks.\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 532, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 493, \"end\": 499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7384483846833748, \"rank\": 0.2916128629181233, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Tokyo Olympics three years ago, Smith was the standout performer, securing two of South Africa's three medals.\", \"from\": 534, \"to\": 651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 623, \"end\": 635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999992311698633, \"rank\": 7.669689042395136e-07, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And she will lead the charge again.\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old former world record holderclocked the third fastest time in historyin the 200m breaststroke at the national championships in Gqeberha in April, and she will line up among the favourites for gold in the French capital.\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 830, \"end\": 838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Elizabeth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gqeberha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Elizabeth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Elizabeth\"}, {\"begin\": 907, \"end\": 913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7384483846833748, \"rank\": 0.2916128629181233, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith will also turn out in the 100m breaststroke, and after bagging silver over two lengths in Tokyo, she should fancy her chances of another podium double.\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1020, \"end\": 1025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999998794892307, \"rank\": 1.2051078608005886e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having climbed the global ranks in recent years, Hatherly is primed to challenge for a medal in the men's cross-country mountain bike contest.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1225, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A former world U-23 champion, Hatherly was 26th at the 2016 Rio Olympics, at the age of 20, and he finished eighth in Tokyo a few years ago.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1345, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999998794892307, \"rank\": 1.2051078608005886e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ranked second in the world this year, he showed his form by winning a World Cup race in France earlier this month, and the 28-year-old rider will be confident of putting up a fight in the chase for medals.\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9998631881903541, \"rank\": 0.0001368156870839845, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has been seven years since the national athletics team earned a medal at a major global championship, and their best chance of breaking the drought will be in the men's 4x400m relay.\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the World Athletics Relays in Bahamas in May, the SA squad took second place in the final, and they have the quality and the depth to shine again in Paris.\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1770, \"end\": 1785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_World_Championships_in_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9885324924408837, \"rank\": 0.011600536802811395, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_World_Championships_in_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_World_Championships_in_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 1796, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"score\": 0.9999999912279236, \"rank\": 8.731168477304354e-09, \"text\": \"Bahamas\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\"}, {\"begin\": 1816, \"end\": 1818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5908077309672434e-18, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1915, \"end\": 1920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.1285026751789862e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And with 400m world record holderWayde van Niekerkrunning the 200m individual event, instead of the 400m, he should have the energy to boost their medal hopes.\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 2082, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A phenom in the world of surfing, Smith missed out on the sport's Olympic debut in Tokyo three years ago due to injury, but he looks ready to represent the country in Paris.\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2167, \"end\": 2172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999998794892307, \"rank\": 1.2051078608005886e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2251, \"end\": 2256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.1285026751789862e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 36-year-old Durbanite has finished among the top five overall in the annual World\\u00a0Surf League six times in his career, and he is currently ranked seventh in the 2024 campaign.\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He might not be among the favourites for gold, but Smith's experience, his consistency and his current form suggest he is in with a shout.\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If bridesmaids were selected for an Olympic wedding, Simbine would be the maid of honour.\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2669, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You will hardly hear his name being mentioned from a global perspective when people discuss potential medallists in the blue riband 100m sprint, but he deserves more credit.\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2844, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 30-year-old national record holder has finished in the top five in the 100m final at the last two editions of the Games, and he'sin shape this year.\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2978, \"end\": 2981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seven_deadly_sins\", \"score\": 0.931105313402834, \"rank\": 0.07344081910678674, \"text\": \"sin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seven_deadly_sins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seven_deadly_sins\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, he will anchor a powerful national team in the 4x100m relay, who also have a podium chance.\", \"from\": 2999, \"to\": 3103, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Middle-distance runner Prudence Sekgodiso\\u00a0is ranked third in the world in the women's 800m event on the track, and she will be confident of putting up a fight, while 20-year-old swimmer Pieter Coetze has an outside chance in the backstroke events.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3128, \"end\": 3136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prudence\", \"score\": 0.9999999980636858, \"rank\": 1.8654988011408147e-09, \"text\": \"Prudence\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prudence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prudence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Former British Open champion Ashleigh Buhai has not been spectacular this year, but she has the experience to shine in the women's golf tournament, and while theybarely managed to qualifyfor the Games, the Blitzboks will be desperate to silence their critics in the men's rugby sevens competition.\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3361, \"end\": 3373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Open_Championship\", \"score\": 0.9887742116405155, \"rank\": 0.011353237398492004, \"text\": \"British Open\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q15061650\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Open_Championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Open_Championship\"}, {\"begin\": 3383, \"end\": 3397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Buhai\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ashleigh Buhai\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Buhai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Buhai\"}, {\"begin\": 3560, \"end\": 3569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Blitzboks\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's rowing pair of John Smith and Christopher Baxter have also displayed good form this season, and they could spring a surprise.\", \"from\": 3653, \"to\": 3788, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3678, \"end\": 3688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Smith_(explorer)\", \"score\": 0.7271469534494619, \"rank\": 0.2756449933545472, \"text\": \"John Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Smith_(explorer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Smith_(explorer)\"}, {\"begin\": 3705, \"end\": 3711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baxter_International\", \"score\": 0.9999784881155477, \"rank\": 1.5311515496226454e-05, \"text\": \"Baxter\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baxter_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baxter_International\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Add The Citizen as a Preferred Source on Google and follow us on Google News to see more of our trusted reporting in Google News and Top Stories.\", \"from\": 3790, \"to\": 3935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3831, \"end\": 3837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9993995031558349, \"rank\": 0.0005900852765415226, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 3855, \"end\": 3866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google News\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\"}, {\"begin\": 3907, \"end\": 3918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google News\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Download our app  Get the latest news and updates on Whatsapp  The latest news directly in your inbox  Support Local Journalism  2026 The Citizen.\", \"from\": 3937, \"to\": 4083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3990, \"end\": 3998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Whatsapp\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.